      <block class="full_text">
        <p>By next April, visitors to Atlantic City may be able to trade a seat at the blackjack table for one in the bleachers. Ground was broken yesterday for a minor league baseball stadium for the Atlantic City Surf, one of seven teams in the independent Atlantic League.</p>
        <p>The Casino Reinvestment Development Authority plans to spend $10.5 million to build the 6,200-seat stadium on part of  Bader Field, a general aviation airport. The city will contribute another $3 million, Mr. Kennedy said. The Federal Aviation Administration, which leases the site to the city, initially opposed the stadium, but was won over after city officials agreed to keep the airport open, James A. Peters, an F.A.A. spokesman, said.</p>
        <p>New Jersey Daily Briefing</p>
      </block>
